Nismond Strongbrew, Brunella's husband and the brains behind the brews at The Tall and the Small, is a gnome with a shock of white hair that defies his youthful appearance. 

Despite his diminutive stature, Nismond has a booming voice that often surprises those who underestimate him.  His eyes twinkle with an inventor's spark, constantly bubbling with ideas for new and exciting concoctions.
Thug is a large, intimidating badger who serves as a (mostly) silent bouncer. He doesn't understand common,

Towering over most patrons, Brunella is a human woman with a booming laugh and even stronger ale. Former bouncer turned barmaid turned owner, she keeps the peace (mostly) with a single raised eyebrow. She seems to be the "tall" part of the Tall and the Small.
A copy of this item (including any crafting you do on it) is used by your Bottled Companion.

Value.value: 'Elp yerself to a drink, my 'usband is a real geinus at this kinna' thing.
Rooms're upstairs if yer too shitfaced to make it home. *She gives you a wink and a playful grin*

value.0: A wiry human with nimble fingers constantly twitching. She spends most of her time nursing a drink and scanning the tavern as new patrons enter.

value.0: Gruff and imposing, Borrok Ironfist is the proprietor of the Relic Hunter's Roost. His single, piercing blue eye is often shadowed by a worn leather eyepatch, a relic of a past adventure gone wrong. Despite his rough exterior, Borrok possesses a keen eye for value and a surprising knowledge of history and myth.
